Final s was in much the same case. It was omitted in verbs before ne interrogative—rogan=rogasne, iuben=iubesne, uiden=uidesne, &c.¹

But magis, mage, potis, pote (like amaris, amare in the 2nd sing. pass.) are distinct forms. The longer forms magis and potis are often written when, before another consonant, position is neglected and the last syllable scanned short. So nimis, satis, miniis, prins, maniiS‚ eris, before consonants.
